# Project Structure Guide

This is a full-stack TypeScript application with separate frontend and backend directories.

## Architecture Overview

- **Backend**: Express.js server with TypeScript located in [backend/](mdc:backend/)

  - Entry point: [backend/bin/www](mdc:backend/bin/www)
  - Main app: [backend/src/app.ts](mdc:backend/src/app.ts)
  - Routes: [backend/src/routes/](mdc:backend/src/routes/)
  - Configuration: [backend/src/config/](mdc:backend/src/config/)

- **Frontend**: Vue.js 3 application with TypeScript located in [frontend/](mdc:frontend/)
  - Entry point: [frontend/src/main.ts](mdc:frontend/src/main.ts)
  - Main component: [frontend/src/App.vue](mdc:frontend/src/App.vue)
  - Components: [frontend/src/components/](mdc:frontend/src/components/)
  - Views: [frontend/src/views/](mdc:frontend/src/views/)
  - Stores (Pinia): [frontend/src/stores/](mdc:frontend/src/stores/)
  - Router: [frontend/src/router/](mdc:frontend/src/router/)

## Key Dependencies

- **Backend**: Express.js, TypeScript, OpenAI integration
- **Frontend**: Vue.js 3, Vuetify, Pinia, Vue Router, Vite

## Development Workflow

- Backend runs on Express server (check [backend/package.json](mdc:backend/package.json) for scripts)
- Frontend uses Vite for development (check [frontend/package.json](mdc:frontend/package.json) for scripts)
- Both use TypeScript with proper configuration files
